parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the air bag warning light can indicate a malfunction in the air bag system, which can lead to the failure of air bags to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The air bag warning light on the dashboard stays on or comes on intermittently
indicating a problem with the air bag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of air bags to deploy in the event of an accident can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: Air bags do not deploy in the event of an accident

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt tensioner can cause the air bag system to malfunction, leading to the failure of air bags to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: causing the air bag warning light to illuminate
and potentially leading to the failure of air bags to deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leading to fatalities.
symptoms: Dimming or complete loss of headlights
while driving at night; headlights only illuminating a short distance ahead; horizontal "shadow line" or dark spot on the road; inability to see pedestrians

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leading to fatalities.
symptoms: Driver-side headlight low beam not projecting properly
creating a dark spot on the road; horizontal "shadow line" or dark spot on the road; inability to see pedestrians

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the headlights to dim or fail, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leading to fatalities.
symptoms: Headlights dimming or failing while driving at night; headlights only illuminating a short distance ahead; inability to see pedestrians
